// Regression test for a known compiler crash: passing a generic function
// call directly as an argument to another call (nested generic calls)
// crashes FIR->FLIR lowering.
//
// Reproduction: println(max(3, 7)) fails with
//   LoweringError: cannot convert T to string
// raised from _to_string() in firescript/flir/lowering.py, reached via
// lower_cast() -> lower_inst(). The generic type parameter T of max<T>
// is apparently not substituted with the concrete instantiated type
// (int32) before the result gets implicitly cast to string for println,
// so the lowering pass sees the literal placeholder "T" as a type name.
//
// Expected (correct) behavior once fixed: prints 7 (max(3, 7)).
import @firescript/std.io.println;
import @firescript/std.math.max;

println(max(3, 7));
